   This is the body of the original message.
   Both the original message and the whole set of REM messages (REM dispatch
   and REM receipts) is built taking inspiration from the various examples
   and excerpt present in the full set of ETSI standards regarding ERDS and
   REM. In particular the ETSI EN 319 532-3 and the ETSI EN 319 532-4 V1.1.3
   (REM baseline) have been used for this purpose.
   Therefore, many values present in the ERDS evidence XMLs and in the
   S/MIME EMLs structures contain "wanted" references (e.g. the initial and
   the final part of any identifier) that are "conserved" in respect to the
   ones present in the standards. This is done in order to allow, when
   desired or possible, a more easy correlation with analogues identifiers
   and elements present in the standards (e.g. Figure A.1 and Figure A.2 of
   the standard ETSI EN 319 532-3, Figure B.9, Figure B.10, Figure B.11,
   Figure B.12, Figure B.13, Figure B.14, Figure B.15, and identifiers
   like sender, recipient(s), S-REMS = Sender REM Service Provider,
   R-REMS = Recipient REM Service Provider from ETSI EN 319 532-4 V1.1.3
   (REM baseline). Thereby, every reference and/or duplication of
   information/identifiers/schemes etc. in respect to the examples of
   the standard can be fall within one of the aforementioned cases
   and/or rationales.
